string.text:
            The %c[pda_white]Garmin eTrex 10%c[ui_gray_1] is a device that can be used to obtain a variety of information about its user.


%c[pda_green]Information%c[ui_gray_1]


This compact device packs a lot of functionalities. It is a very good tool to get around the Zone, given its high reliability against psi-emissions.


Functionalities:

• %c[pda_white]Compass%c[ui_gray_1] : shows the heading of the user;

• %c[pda_white]Speed%c[ui_gray_1] : the current speed (in %c[pda_white]km/h%c[ui_gray_1]) of the user;

• %c[pda_white]Dist to Next%c[ui_gray_1] : the distance (in %c[pda_white]km%c[ui_gray_1]) to the waypoint;

• %c[pda_white]ETA at Dest%c[ui_gray_1] : the time (%c[pda_white]24h%c[ui_gray_1] format) at which the user will arrive at the waypoint;

• %c[pda_white]Time to Next%c[ui_gray_1] : the time needed (in %c[pda_white]HH:mm%c[ui_gray_1], or %c[pda_white]mm:ss%c[ui_gray_1] if less than an hour) to get to the waypoint.


By default, the compass' cursor is fixed and its background indicates the heading. But can be changed to lock north and have the cursor rotate instead.

            The %c[pda_white]Flea Market%c[ui_gray_1] allows the player to purchase temporary offers, where items come in multiple units, but at a discount.


%c[pda_green]Information%c[ui_gray_1]


By talking to a trader at the Flea Market, the player has the option to purchase special offers. These offers are limited in time, and will eventually expire and get replaced with newer offers.


Offers consist of the following:


• %c[pda_white]Item%c[ui_gray_1]. The item contained in the offer;

• %c[pda_white]Quantity%c[ui_gray_1]. The quantity of the item contained in the offer. Randomized between 2 and 10 items;

• %c[pda_white]Discount%c[ui_gray_1]. The discount applied compared to the regular price. Randomized between 5% and 50%;

• %c[pda_white]Price%c[ui_gray_1]. The money required to accept the offer.
